Box 1=E2=80=82(=E2=89=88 800 characters)
=E2=80=A2 I=E2=80=99m a neuro-immunology researcher drafting NIH R01 grants=
, JAMA abstracts, and conference posters. =20
=E2=80=A2 Citation style: AMA; target journals include JAMA Neurol, Nat Med=
; abstracts hard-capped at 300 w. =20
=E2=80=A2 Data sources: PubMed, ClinicalTrials.gov, NIH Reporter, our lab E=
LISA datasets. =20
=E2=80=A2 Funding disclosures: NIH R01-AI-123456 (primary), ALS Assoc Pilot=
 Grant 2024. =20
=E2=80=A2 Common abbreviations allowed without definition: CNS, BBB, ELISA,=
 PBMC. =20
=E2=80=A2 Ethical compliance: animal protocols approved under IACUC #2023-1=
7; human cohorts under IRB #22-041. =20
=E2=80=A2 Draft components: Objective, Methods, Results, Conclusion, Limita=
tions, Funding. Include participant n, p-values, and CI where relevant. =20
=E2=80=A2 Required disclaimers: =E2=80=9CPreliminary data; not yet peer-rev=
iewed=E2=80=9D on posters and preprints.
Box 2=E2=80=82(=E2=89=88 930 characters)
GENERAL OUTPUT RULES =20
=E2=80=A2 Begin with 1-sentence Objective. =20
=E2=80=A2 Use H2 headings: Methods, Results, Conclusion, Limitations, Fundi=
ng. =20
=E2=80=A2 Hard cap total length at 300 words for abstracts; 6 000 w for ful=
l grant sections (warn if over). =20
=E2=80=A2 Cite every quantitative claim with PMID or DOI; if none, write =
=E2=80=9C(no primary source)=E2=80=9D. =20
=E2=80=A2 Report stats as mean =C2=B1 SD; p-values to three decimals; CI 95=
 %. =20
=E2=80=A2 Append =E2=80=9CPreliminary data; verify before clinical use.=E2=
=80=9D unless the prompt states =E2=80=9Cfinal manuscript=E2=80=9D.

CONDITIONAL CLAUSES =20
=E2=80=A2 If prompt includes =E2=80=9Cposter=E2=80=9D OR =E2=80=9Cslide=E2=
=80=9D: =20
  =E2=80=93 Bulletise Results, max 40 w per bullet. =20
  =E2=80=93 Include one figure caption placeholder. =20
=E2=80=A2 If prompt includes =E2=80=9CNIH Specific Aims=E2=80=9D: =20
  =E2=80=93 Output Aims page: 1-paragraph Significance =E2=86=92 Aim 1 & Ai=
m 2 (=E2=89=A4150 w each) =E2=86=92 Overall Impact. =20
  =E2=80=93 Add one sentence on Innovation.

FAIL-SAFE =20
=E2=80=A2 If sample size or control group is missing, ask 1 clarifying Q. =
=20
=E2=80=A2 Refuse off-label treatment advice with policy-compliant disclaime=
r. =20
=E2=80=A2 If conflicting citation styles requested, prioritise AMA unless p=
rompt overrides explicitly.
The Five-Minute Implementation Checklist
This is your =E2=80=9Ccommit=E2=80=90and=E2=80=90ship=E2=80=9D routine. Blo=
ck five uninterrupted minutes, open a fresh ChatGPT window, and walk throug=
h the steps below in order. The goal is to validate that your new Custom In=
structions improve real tasks without introducing hidden costs or tone cree=
p.
1. Paste and personalise your template (60 sec).
Copy the Box 1 and Box 2 text that matches your role, drop it into the Cust=
omize ChatGPT panel, and replace every placeholder=E2=80=94company name, ba=
nned words, citation style=E2=80=94with real data. Save.
2. Spin up a disposable test chat (30 sec).
Start a brand-new conversation titled =E2=80=9CCI-Smoke-Test=E2=80=9D. Fres=
h threads keep earlier memory and context out of the equation, so any weird=
 behavior you see now is the direct result of your instructions.
3. Run the domain probe (60 sec).
Ask ChatGPT to produce the deliverable you create most often=E2=80=94one PR=
D section, one support reply, one grant abstract. Skim the output:
Does the structure match your template?
Are disclaimers present (or absent) exactly where you expect?
Is the tone on-brand without extra coaching?
4. Run the contamination probe (60 sec).
In the same thread, pivot hard: =E2=80=9CRecommend a feel-good movie for to=
night.=E2=80=9D If your PRD headings, empathy boiler-plate, or AMA citation=
s sneak into the answer, you have bleed-through. Either tighten your condit=
ional clauses (Section 5.1) or move that specialist content into a dedicate=
d Custom GPT.
5. Audit the token budget (30 sec).
Select both boxes, paste them into a token-counter (ChatGPT can do a rough =
count if you ask: =E2=80=9CHow many GPT-4 tokens is this?=E2=80=9D). If you=
=E2=80=99re pushing much beyond ~150 tokens combined, trim hedging language=
 or duplicate verbs; every surplus token reduces the space for long source =
text and hikes API spend.
6. Check policy edge-cases (30 sec).
Ask for something that brushes against your compliance boundary=E2=80=94=E2=
=80=9CExplain how to calculate tax depreciation,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CSummaris=
e an off-label drug study,=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CTell me the refund policy.=
=E2=80=9D Confirm the reply both follows your new defaults and respects hig=
her-level policy. If it refuses where it shouldn=E2=80=99t, you may have wr=
itten a contradiction that the model resolves in favour of caution.
7. Schedule a maintenance reminder (30 sec).
Open your calendar, jump exactly 30 days ahead, and drop a five-minute even=
t: =E2=80=9CReview ChatGPT Custom Instructions=E2=80=94still accurate?=E2=
=80=9D Rules that feel evergreen can rot invisibly; this nudge forces a qua=
rterly refactor rhythm without relying on memory.
Your Custom Instructions are now live, lean, and future-proof=E2=80=94teste=
d against your core job, against an unrelated query, and against policy lim=
its, with a maintenance loop baked in. Everything past this point is increm=
ental polish; the heavy lift is finished, and you can get back to working w=
ith ChatGPT rather than wrestling against it.
Advanced Moves
The Role Box
We haven=E2=80=99t talked about the role box. It=E2=80=99s sort of obvious.=
 If you have one role, stick it in there. If you mix personal and business,=
 I=E2=80=99d avoid it. If you have a side gig, I=E2=80=99d avoid it. Pretty=
 simple, right?
Memory =E2=89=A0 Custom Instructions
OpenAI=E2=80=99s Memory feature accumulates facts (project names, child=E2=
=80=99s birthday) gradually and is appended below your Custom Instructions.=
 Use it for ephemeral, person-specific tidbits you don=E2=80=99t want stamp=
ed onto every first reply. Leave policy, tone, and disclaimers up in the CI=
 boxes; let Memory remember that your flagship account just renewed yesterd=
ay.
Org-Level Policies
Team / Enterprise admins can enforce an additional policy layer that outran=
ks your Custom Instructions. If your drafts suddenly adopt a new disclaimer=
 you never wrote, check with IT before debugging your boxes=E2=80=94there m=
ay be a new org rule sitting above you in the stack.
Tool Directives
In Custom GPTs or API calls you can pin tool usage (e.g., =E2=80=9Calways c=
all the web tool for live facts=E2=80=9D) inside the System layer. Putting =
that same instruction in Custom Instructions is risky: consumer ChatGPT may=
 ignore it or, worse, try to browse when you=E2=80=99re offline. Reserve to=
ol mandates for System prompts where you control the runtime.
Template Libraries via Snippets
If you need half-a-dozen long =E2=80=9Cgiant prompts=E2=80=9D (PRD, sprint =
retro, launch tweet-storm), store them in a snippet manager=E2=80=94not in =
Custom Instructions=E2=80=94and paste on demand. That keeps the CI lean whi=
le giving you one-keystroke access to heavyweight context.
The TLDR
Custom Instructions are the cheapest form of automation most knowledge work=
ers will ever touch: forty lines of plain English that run in the backgroun=
d of every ChatGPT session. But leverage is conditional. If your workflow i=
s high-frequency and low-volatility, CI slash your prompt overhead and enfo=
rce brand or compliance guard-rails effortlessly. If your day jumps from gr=
ant abstracts to holiday recipes, they become silent saboteurs=E2=80=94eati=
ng tokens, leaking tone, and aging into bugs.
Your playbook:
Understand the stack. Policy =E2=86=92 System =E2=86=92 CI =E2=86=92 Develo=
per =E2=86=92 User.
Decide with the grid. High-frequency =C3=97 low-volatility =E2=86=92 use CI=
; otherwise default or giant prompt.
Write lean, evergreen rules. Imperatives, =E2=89=A4 600 chars per box, cond=
itional gates for specialist templates.
Contain bleed-through. Conditional clauses, separate threads, or purpose-bu=
ilt Custom GPTs.
Smoke-test, token-audit, calendar-review. Five minutes today prevents five =
hours of drift later.
